Presented by Gary Imlach, Chris Boardman and Ned Boulting. Commentary: Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen. Final Stage highlights, Rambouillet to Paris Champs-Elysees. A rare final stage with a couple of early climbs that will finish off the King of the Mountains competition. Then, the traditional eight and a half laps around central Paris before the most prestigious sprint of the race, won in the past three years by Britain's world champion Mark Cavendish.
